Reasoning: The paper investigates the effect of network structure on performance in complex problem-solving tasks, which involves both search for information and search for theories. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges inherent in manipulating network structure to enhance performance, which may fall under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper also uses an experimental platform to measure information and solutions separately, which may relate to the sub-category of Computing and Computational Science (cs.CC) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
